  <properties>
    <property name="family">Access Control Auxiliary Controller</property>
    <property name="variant">Red Aux 8</property>
    <property name="part number">A8</property>
    <property name="dimensions">Red Max 1:1 calibrated 3.0895 in x 2.8192 in</property>
    <property name="terminal pitch assumption">5.08 mm</property>
    <property name="mounting pattern">Lower narrow Red Max slot</property>
    <property name="mounting hole spacing">1.8512 in x 1.9002 in</property>
    <property name="calibration source">Red Max exact 1368 x 1752 px image at 96 DPI</property>
    <property name="SVG coordinate density">72 units per inch</property>
    <property name="renderer compatibility">Plain default SVG namespace; no generated ns0 prefixes</property>
  </properties>
  <description>PDK Red Aux 8 eight-port auxiliary controller, part number A8. Estimated assembly footprint is 5.60 x 5.36 inches, calculated from the repeated removable terminal spacing using an assumed 5.08 mm terminal pitch. The part includes eight assignable inputs, eight 5 A Form-C relay outputs, eight wet/dry jumper blocks, main 12 to 24 VDC power, and a logical two-pin battery connector. Intended for wiring diagrams and enclosure-layout documentation only. Recalibrated against the exact 1368 x 1752 px, 96 DPI Red Max enclosure artwork. Target pattern: Lower narrow Red Max slot; mounting-hole spacing 1.8512 x 1.9002 inches. Resulting breadboard footprint: 3.0895 x 2.8192 inches. This revision removes generated namespace prefixes that can break Qt/Fritzing SVG rendering and normalizes every SVG view to 72 coordinate units per physical inch, matching established Fritzing part conventions.</description>
